        "description": {
          "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>The skulk is &amp;Reference[condition=invisible]. This invisibility can be circumvented by three things:</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><ul class=\"rd__list rd__list-hang-notitle\"><li class=\"rd__li \"><p class=\"rd__p-list-item\"><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Charnel Candles.</span> The skulk appears as a dim, translucent form in the light of a candle made of fat rendered from a corpse whose identity is unknown.</p></li><li class=\"rd__li \"><p class=\"rd__p-list-item\"><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Children.</span> Humanoid children, aged 10 and under, can see through this invisibility.</p></li><li class=\"rd__li \"><p class=\"rd__p-list-item\"><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Reflective Surfaces.</span> The skulk appears as a drab, smoothskinned biped if its reflection can be seen in a mirror or on another surface.</p></li></ul></div>",
